wd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Copyright 1983 The New York Times Company.  All Rights Reserved.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 A recent article entitled ''Airport Expansion Under New Attack'' (Nov. 13) that cites the efforts of what is purported to be ''a new opposition group'' - Coalition Against Westchester County Airport Expansion - raises grave concern for those of us who seek rational and objective resolution to the many issues surrounding the future of Westchester County Airport.  \par \par \uc2 In a recent letter and brochure sent to area corporations by the organization, it purported to represent tens of thousands of concerned citizens and organizations in Westchester and Fairfield counties. We feel the organization not only has grossly exaggerated the numbers it represents but also has presented a shopworn case comprised of inflammatory statements, emotional appeals and deliberate misrepresentation of facts to justify opposition to adoption of the County Airport master plan.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The coalition opposes improvement of the airport's ground facilities as proposed in the master plan, implying that such improvements would ''create another La Guardia in our backyard.'' This is a ridiculous and unfounded conclusion when one recognizes that traffic at Westchester County Airport has actually declined by 30 percent in the past decade.  \par \par \uc2 The Chamber believes the improvements proposed in the master plan are carefully designed to discourage anything even remotely resembling a La Guardia operation. To the contrary, they most clearly are proposed to improve airport efficiency and safety within the confines of the  \par \par \uc2 existing and  \par \par \uc2 not an expanded facility. They constitute improvements long needed to serve the 1,000 plus people who use the facility daily. They are needed to further insure minimum noise impact and safe operation of the 400 or so private and business aircraft based at the facility and used by area companies that provide more than 45,000 jobs and generate payrolls in excess of one billion dollars to the area's economy.  \par \par \uc2 We view the coalition's letter to area corporations seeking support for its efforts as a shoddy attempt to entrap those corporations based upon an infounded implication that their failure to respond would reflect a lack of ''neighborly fair play, social responsibility and corporate citizenship.'' Nothing could be further from the truth!  \par \par \uc2 The Westchester business community has always been a leader in exercising \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  and meeting its obligations as good neighbors and citizens. In fact, the County Chamber and the companies it represents - many of whom are among the largest in the nation and recognized for their social and community commitment - have continually demonstrated their determination to be good corporate citizens and pursue a policy of neighborly concern and fair play.  \par \par \uc2 The success of the current voluntary operation restrictions and the efforts of the County Chamber, its member companies in cooperation with the Westchester Aviation Association, et. al., to monitor, encourage and insure compliance to noise abatement procedures vividly demonstrate this commitment. In fact, the airport is getting quieter all the time through considerable investment by these corporate good neighbors as they bring new quiet-generation aircraft to the field to replace older and noisier equipment.  \par \par \uc2 The coalition's efforts to block ground improvements proposed in the master plan - particularly the recommendation that a new parallel runway be constructed - represent uniformed opposition to one of the most important safety and noise abatement considerations in the master plan. The coalition draws upon the conclusion reached in the recent Thompson Crenshaw report to support their position.  \par \par \uc2 The County Chamber believes the Thompson Crenshaw conclusion that there is no need for a parallel runway because of the ISL and ATC improvements is in error. Studies have clearly shown the contribution of parallel runways to the safe operation of an airport. Quite obviously, Thompson Crenshaw in conducting its study was unaware that aircraft at the County Airport were still experiencing airborne and ground delays resulting from aircraft mix problems related to the facility's one-runway operation and crossed two-runway system.  \par \par \uc2 When aircraft are delayed in this way, safety is compromised and pollution and noise exposure are increased. Although there will always be some noise generated by the airport, without the parallel runway operators will be hampered in their ability to reduce noise to its lowest possible level and potentially unsafe conditions will continue to exist. One need only ask the air controllers who deal with these problems daily to verify this view.  \par \par \uc2 In the view of the County Chamber's Airport Committee, the coalition's commitment to political pressures and court action represents an unwarranted obstruction of what is desperately needed and long overdue. The only possible result if their efforts are to be heeded is the continued operating inefficiency of Westchester County Airport and the needless waste of taxpayer funds. The ultimate impact is on the safety, the local \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , the economy and the residents of the County.  \par \par \uc2 The County Chamber of Commerce and its County Airport Committee vigorously support and urge adoption of the County Airport Master Plan. We feel the improvements it proposes are long overdue and that the County should not be swayed by the emotional appeals and obstructionist tactics of a small vocal minority that has stifled improvements at Westchester County Airport too long.  \par \par \uc2 It's time to move ahead so the benefits of the improvements can accrue to the County as a whole. Statesmanship and objective leadership are now needed to avoid sacrificing the needs and rights of an overwhelming majority of Westchester citizens and corporations to appease a small, misguided but vocal minority.  \par \par \uc2 We hope you will agree. EDWIN C. FOX Jr. Chairman County Airport Committee County Chamber of Commerce  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\