o and other black townships. And most black teachers are sorely underqualified: One recent survey determined that 80 percent of black secondary school teachers had themselves never received the equivalent of a high school diploma.  \par \par \uc2 Now, a growing number of American corporations are making black education their concern. And they are doing so in ways that go far beyond slapdash, undirected spending.  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Hewlett-Packard, for one, once supported education by giving computer equipment to a black teachers' training college. Now, says Simon Middleton, \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  director, the company has realized that ''for the most part, computers are irrelevant in a third world \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 .'' Hewlett-Packard now focuses most of its education support on the development of Protec, a technical education program for 300 students that concentrates on the development of practical job skills and on ''attitudinal enrichment'' through exposure to activities outside the black township.  \par \par \uc2 For its part, Mobil S.A. is concentrating more on the teachers than on the students, in the belief that more competent teachers will encourage youths to continue their education, says Pat O'Malley, who oversees the company's social responsibility projects. Mobil has helped to develop and finance teacher opportunity programs (TOPS), which provide classroom training for teachers to help them increase both their own knowledge and their teaching skills.  \par \par \uc2 Similarly, a project financed jointly by Burroughs-Memorex and Johnson & Johnson aims to upgrade the quality of science teaching at the seventh grade level in 44 area schools. ''If you're teaching someone and you're not qualified yourself, then you're batting off a loose wicket,'' said Ian Burton, public relations director of Burroughs-Memorex.  \par \par \uc2 Still, doubts remain about how much multinationals can accomplish in raising the caliber of black teachers in South Africa. ''American companies can only be pilot project initiators,'' said Mr. Burton. ''We cannot solve the black education problem, educating six million black children.''  \par \par \uc2 And some wonder whether corporations are spreading their dollars too thin between programs for teachers, students and schools. ''The thing I find difficult with the way companies go about it is they have no clear vision about what they're moving toward,'' said Brother Neil McGurk, principal of Sacred Heart College, a multi-racial secondary school.  \par \par \uc2 Drawing  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gedu : \uc2 Education | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctl