spalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 From Mr David Grayson.\par \par \uc2 Sir, If Martin Wolf ("Sleep-walking with the enemy", May 16) believes that \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  is principally being promoted by anti-business non-governmental organisations, he should get out more often!\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Across the world, it is business-run organisations that are championing CSR. They recognise that encouraging higher business standards on the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , diversity and human rights, community involvement and so on is the best way of preserving open markets and a pro-enterprise climate; and of building trust in, and the reputation of, individual companies. Rather than raising costs, as Mr Wolf argues, much CSR, for example on waste management or staff development, will save costs.\par \par \uc2 The increased expectations on how a business runs its own affairs and contributes to tackling societal problems is coming from consumers, employees, investors, local communities - not just from NGOs. And yes - even though Mr Wolf may not like it - the collapse of totalitarian regimes and ideologies, has led to an explosion in the number and influence of NGOs. This is not undemocratic, but part of a more pluralist democracy.\par \par \uc2 Mr Wolf quotes an unnamed chief executive telling a competitor: "My business is run by Greenpeace today and it is my job to ensure that Greenpeace is running yours tomorrow." Leaving aside that any chief executive who hands over the running of his business will be rightly sacked by the owners, it is a complete parody to suggest CSR means abdicating management to an external pressure group! Rather, it is the intelligent balancing of stakeholder interests and concerns, which in turn will, in the long term, best protect shareholder value.\par \par \uc2 David Grayson, 19 Gilbert Road, London SE11 4NZ. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nlet : \uc2 Letter | nrgn : \uc2 Routine General News\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 eurz : \uc2 Europe | uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | weurz : \uc2 Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpa