spnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 A dynamic economy and fair society were not enemies but partners, Patricia Hewitt, trade and industry secretary, said when presenting the annual Business in the Community awards for excellence last night.\par \par \uc2 Policies to promote social justice, she said, were the same as those needed to create a successful modern economy. By integrating social responsibility into activities such as recruitment, procurement, the supply chain, training and employment practices, companies could contribute to building high-performance, high-productivity workplaces.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Award winners included Richard Lambert, editor of the Financial Times, who received a Prince of Wales's ambassador award. Ambassador awards - a personal choice of the prince, president of BITC - go to individuals making distinctive contributions to \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The BITC awards are organised in association with the Financial Times and Mr Lambert, who will relinquish the editorship in the autumn after 10 years, has been active in encouraging the business community to adopt a rigorous approach to social responsibility.\par \par \uc2 He received his award for his commitment to promoting the measurement and reporting of the impact of companies' social programmes.\par \par \uc2 Sir Neville Simms, chairman of Carillion, also received an ambassador award for sustained and active commitment to activities in the West Midlands. His involvement includes setting up an employers' forum to work with the community in Birmingham's Balsall Heath district.\par \par \uc2 This year's impact on society award - the company of the year - went to the Co-operative Bank. Runner-up Camelot was highly commended by the judges.\par \par \uc2 Co-operative Bank is a leader in independently-audited social reporting. In a significant innovation this year, the bank compiled a cost-benefit analysis of social responsibility, calculating that up to 18 per cent of its #96.3m pre-tax profit in 2000 could be "reasonably attributed" to positive ethical and ecological policies.\par \par \uc2 The analysis takes account of factors such as the cost of turning away business the bank regards as ethically unacceptable - ecological impact is the most frequent ground for declining business, followed by involvement with the arms trade and animal welfare issues.\par \par \uc2 On the positive side, it says more than 20 per cent of Co-operative Bank customers have been influenced to open accounts for ethical and ecological reasons.\par \par \uc2 Winners of the programme impact awards: cause-related marketing - Bettys &Taylors of Harrogate; focused action - Lloyds TSB; innovation - Tesco; investing in young people - Lattice; neighbourhood renewal - Lloyds TSB; global leadership - TV Globo, Brazil; power in partnership - Lattice and Groundwork UK.\par \par \uc2 Winners of the business excellence awards: \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  - 3M United Kingdom; community investment - ASAS, Capital One; diversity - JP Morgan; i