rved \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The US, once a leader in promoting global business ethics, has been overtaken by European governments and companies, according to a study by the National Policy Association, a Washington-based non-profit public policy organisation, writes Alison Maitland.\par \par \uc2 The study examined the attitudes of the US and five European Union nations - Austria, Belgium, Denmark, the Netherlands and the UK - to corporate responsibility. "The Europeans have sprung ahead and are creating a different corporate \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 ," says Susan Aaronson, co-author and senior fellow of the NPA.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 This is ironic since \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  (CSR) was "made in the USA", claims the study. US pharmaceuticals groups wrote codes of conduct in the late 19th century saying their main objective was to serve public health and, by doing so, to make profits. In 1977, Reverend Leon Sullivan, an American minister, developed his human rights code for companies operating in apartheid South Africa, which he expanded into the Global Sullivan Principles of Social Responsibility. By the 1980s, more than 100 US mutual and investment funds screened investments by companies' human rights or environmental record.\par \par \uc2 In recent years, however, European policymakers have taken a wide range of measures to promote CSR, the study says. UK law, for example, now requires pension funds to disclose how they view social, ethical and environmental issues in their investment decisions. The Danish government set up The Copenhagen Centre to encourage social partnerships between business, government and non-government bodies.\par \par \uc2 Many European companies now see CSR as a way to retain good employees, to win consumer and brand loyalty, to reduce risks and to build goodwill with the public and investors.\par \par \uc2 Ms Aaronson and her co-author James Reeves argue that these practices pose a challenge to the competitiveness of US multinationals. They believe they can be explained by a difference in business culture. "European firms are more comfortable working with government to improve social conditions and they are more comfortable in a regulated \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . Business expects government will ask more of them and government does ask more of business."\par \par \uc2 The European Response to Public Demands for Global Corporate Responsibility, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.multinational"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.multinational}}}\uc2  guidelines.org/csr/. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\