ustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 How do chief executives view the debate about \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 ? Is it largely a public relations exercise, and how relevant is it to the bottom line?\par \par \uc2 These questions, asked of more than 1,100 chief executives from 33 countries in PwC's recent Global CEO Survey, are, of course, related, writes Alison Maitland.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 A public relations disaster, based on irresponsible or ill-judged actions, can drive away customers, shareholders and even employees.\par \par \uc2 Just over half the CEOs disagreed that all that was entailed was well managed "spin". Of these, 26 per cent felt strongly that \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  had to have substance.\par \par \uc2 Yet 28 per cent of respondents saw some merit in the argument that this is predominantly a PR issue, a minority view that was particularly apparent among European chief executives.\par \par \uc2 The survey revealed greater consensus on the impact on financial performance. Sixty-eight per cent of CEOs agreed the proper exercise of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  was vital to companies' profitability.\par \par \uc2 "Whether it is a matter of substance or more a matter of public relations positioning, the company's reputation in this regard does affect profitability," says PwC, which carried out the survey in conjunction with the World Economic Forum.\par \par \uc2 These findings reinforce the view that CSR is still driven more by concern about the negative consequences of ignoring reputation than by the potential benefits of embracing "responsible" behaviour. This may be because it is easier to grasp the former - and there are plenty of high-profile examples of it.\par \par \uc2 Views are still taking shape, however. Twenty-one per cent of CEOs declared themselves unsure whether this was mainly a public relations issue; 19 per cent were uncertain whether profits depended on it.\par \par \uc2 It does not simplify matters that \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  or reputation is interpreted differently around the world. North American business leaders said responsible action towards stakeholders and support for community projects were more important in influencing social reputation than was the creation of shareholder value.\par \par \uc2 CEOs in Europe and in Latin America thought the most important component was a sound working \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , followed by responsible action towards stakeholders.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.pwcglobal.com"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.pwcglobal.com}}}\uc2 . \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\asp