pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 SURVEY - BITC AWARDS 2002 - Good imprint on the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  - BUSINESS IMPACT AWARDS - Many of the entries stress the benefits of volunteering for their own staff.\par \par \uc2 * Business in the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  (sponsored by National Grid) The Beacon Press uses good practice and innovative technology to reduce pollution and waste, differentiating itself in a competitive print-ing industry with a generally poor environmental record. Its novel systems include alcohol-and water-free printing, and it shares its knowledge with peers, customers, suppliers and environmental groups.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The Co-operative Bank, responding to customer feedback, declines to invest in any business that relies for its core activity on producing fossil fuels. It has cut its own emissions of global warming gases and invests in restoring wildlife habitats.\par \par \uc2 Scottish Power is changing its generation mix to reduce CO emissions, particularly by developing wind farms in the UK and US. It is cleaning up its coal-fired power generation and introducing energy-efficiency programmes, notably for low-income households.\par \par \uc2 * International business leaders forum award (sponsored by Diageo) GlaxoSmithKline is the single finalist for this award for international corporate citizenship for its Personal Hygiene and Sanitation Education (Phase) initiative, in Kenya, Uganda, Nicaragua and Peru.\par \par \uc2 The project aims to stop diarrhoeal disease, a big but easily preventable killer of children, through education and advice on hand-washing.\par \par \uc2 * Community investment (sponsored by the Department of Health, in association with Home Office Active Community Unit) AOL (UK) has a dedicated community investment team, focusing on supporting charities that help socially excluded people to use the internet and raising policymakers' awareness of the digital divide.\par \par \uc2 Seventy per cent of employees at Bain &Company took part in community activities last year, including pro bono consulting, mentoring heads of voluntary bodies and introducing business to GCSE students.\par \par \uc2 Bupa's Community Connections programme gives employees a range of options for involvement in their neighbourhoods. Community activity is included in management training.\par \par \uc2 Focusing on responsible drinking, the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and community involvement, Diageo has established three charities to tackle social exclusion and supports tools to measure community investment.\par \par \uc2 KPMG's staff volunteering includes mentoring schoolchildren, preparing homeless people for work and coaching disadvantaged young people in interview skills. Volunteers' efforts are recognised in appraisals.\par \par \uc2 Tesco has formed 13 partnerships in Scotland, northern England and London under its Regeneration Programme to help jobless people back to work in deprived neighbourhoods where it builds new stores. (See also Neighbourhood renewal in Community Impact awards article.)\par \par \uc2 * Diversity (sponsored by Procter &Gamble) Barclays' diversity projects include an online register to assist job-sharing, the voluntary extension of retirement from 60 to 65 years, harassment support volunteers and "multi-faith rooms". (See also Realising ability in Community Impact awards article.)\par \par \uc2 The approach of West Bromwich Building Society is to "promote understanding, tolerance and flexibility and aim for cultural harmony". Using positive action and strong support from the top, it has significantly increased the number of women and ethnic minority branch managers.\par \par \uc2 * Positive impact (sponsored by Lloyds TSB, in association with the Small Business Service) Brahm, a communications consultancy operating in the Yorkshire and Humber region, is one of three finalists for this award for small and medium-sized companies. Brahm gave BITC's Right to Read programme an identity and website and arranged free advertising.\par \par \uc2 Flag, a communications company in Cambridge, has established a Reading Buddies scheme with local schools, developed links with arts organisations and worked to reduce its environmental impact, treating all of this as part of the way it does business.\par \par \uc2 Viridian Nutrition, founded on a belief in responsible business, gives half its net profits to environmental and children's charities. It aims to offer quality products that cost no more than mainstream brands, using recycled glass packaging and organic ingredients wherever possible.\par \par \uc2 * Special awards Two nomination awards will be made: the Prince of Wales's Ambassador award, for an individual who has demonstrated leadership in \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , and the Sieff Award, sponsored by Marks and Spencer, for an outstanding community partner.\par \par \uc2 * Impact on society (in association with the Centre for Tomorrow's Company) KPMG and Scottish Power are the finalists. (See main article.)\par \par \uc2 2. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c31 : \uc2 Marketing | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | genv : \uc2 Environmental News\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 eecz : \uc2 European Union Countries | eurz : \uc2 Europe | uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | weurz : \uc2 Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IPC\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 2 | SURVEY - BITC AWARDS 2002 | Awards | Company News | Strategy | Beacon Press | Bupa | Co-operative Bank | GlaxoSmithKline PLC | United Kingdom | European Union | Europe