ing, I sincerely believe legislation is the only way to produce the step-change needed if business is to improve its social responsibility record and restore the public's trust."\par \par \uc2 His call will be controversial with business organisations, which have resisted the idea of "excessive" government intervention in \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The Co-operative Bank is a leader in independently audited social reporting, and yesterday was named the world's most socially responsible business in the Corporate Conscience Awards - which are run by Social Accountability International, a human rights organisation - in New York.\par \par \uc2 Mr Pedelty's comments came as Scottish Power, the energy supplier, was awarded the title of company of the year by Business in the Community for making responsible practices "part of its DNA".\par \par \uc2 The company received its accolade from the Prince of Wales as part of the annual BITC Awards for Excellence, organised in association with the Financial Times.\par \par \uc2 Julia Cleverdon, BITC chief executive, said: "Scottish Power seem to be well ahead of the game in environmental reporting and in addressing a range of impacts on customers, communities and existing and potential employees."\par \par \uc2 Ambassador awards, chosen by the Prince of Wales, BITC's president, were given to Mike Mills, chief executive of Ulster Carpets, and Sir Nicholas Montagu, chairman of the Inland Revenue. Mr Mills has spearheaded BITC's campaign in Northern Ireland, while Sir Nicholas has led staff volunteering and diversity initiatives that have helped change the culture inside the Revenue.\par \par \uc2 Mike Tyler, director of Tower Hamlets Education Business Partnership, won the Sieff award, sponsored by Marks and Spencer, for the community-based individual or organisation that has best collaborated with the corporate sector to benefit society. Winners of the business impact awards were: \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  - The Beacon Press; community investment - Bain &Co; international corporate citizenship - Glaxo-SmithKline; positive impact by small and medium-sized companies - Brahm. Winners of the community impact awards were: cause-related marketing - Centrica; homelessness - Bank of Scotland/Big Issue; investing in potential - Scottish Power Learning; neighbourhood renewal - UBS Warburg; disability - Centrica, Lloyds TSB. London Electricity won the innovation award.\par \par \uc2 London Edition 2. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility | ghum : \uc2 Human Rights/Civil Liberties | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | gcom : \uc2 Society/Community/Work | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfcpex : \uc2 FC&E Executive News Filter\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 eecz : \uc2 European Union Countries | eurz : \uc2 Europe | uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | weurz : \uc2 Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\