inance for developing environmental technologies Use equity ownership to promote \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  Provide financial products to disadvantaged and developing communities.\par \par \uc2 In the UK there have been a number of product innovations to encourage sustainable development. There have been a number of new funds from Morley Fund Management, Friends Ivory &Sime, Jupiter Asset Management and Merrill Lynch Investment Management investing in ethical companies.\par \par \uc2 HSBC has set up a sell-side research unit and Schroders a buy-side investment process to incorporate socially responsible investment (SRI). Norfolk County Council gave a GBP300m ethical mandate to SG Asset Management.\par \par \uc2 The principles will be promoted around the world under a memorandum of understanding with between the principles and the UN Environmental Programme Financial Initiative to be signed by Mr Blair.\par \par \uc2 Karina Litvack, director of corporate governance and socially responsible investment at Friends Ivory &Sime, said: "This initiative has the support in the right places and is a positive statement of aspirational principles."\par \par \uc2 As well as the existing 10 groups that have already signed up, to the principles, (see table), others are expected to join before the summit meeting.\par \par \uc2 The Corporation of London, on behalf of the government, commissioned the Forum for the Future's Centre for Sustainable Investment to complete the project. The Forum interviewed. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\in