 Blair, UK prime minister, will formally unveil the London Principles at the World Summit on Sustainable Development, held next week in Johannesburg, South Africa.\par \par \uc2 The principles are:\par \par \uc2 * Provide access to finance and risk management\par \par \uc2 * Promote transparency and high standards of corporate governance\par \par \uc2 * Reflect the cost of environmental and social risks in financial products\par \par \uc2 * Use equity ownership to promote efficient and sustainable asset use\par \par \uc2 * Provide access to finance for developing environmental technologies\par \par \uc2 * Use equity ownership to promote \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\par \par \uc2 * Provide financial products to disadvantaged and developing communities.\par \par \uc2 The principles will be promoted around the world under a memorandum of understanding with the UN Environmental Programme Financial Initiative to be signed by Mr Blair.\par \par \uc2 As well as the 10 groups already signed up to the principles, others are expected to join before the summit meeting.\par \par \uc2 The Corporation of London, on behalf of the government, commissioned the Forum for the Future's Centre for Sustainable Investment to complete the project. The Forum interviewed 50 companies. James Mawson\par \par \uc2 1. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 c13 : \uc2 Regulation/Government Policy | ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | genv : \uc2 Environmental News\cell \par